message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The hypoplastic nasal bone and abnormal maternal serum studies suggest Down syndrome. Among the possible physical findings listed in the options, a single transverse palmar crease is commonly associated with Down syndrome. Ambiguous external genitalia suggests a disorder of sexual development, extremity lymphedema suggests Turner syndrome, and meningomyelocele suggests neural tube defects.
